<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
<title>SpatiumDDI Appliance</title>
<style>
  :root { color-scheme: dark light; }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: -apple-system, "Segoe UI", system-ui, sans-serif;
    background: #0f172a;
    color: #e2e8f0;
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
  }
  .card {
    max-width: 640px;
    width: 100%;
    background: #1e293b;
    border: 1px solid #334155;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.35);
  }
  h1 {
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem 0;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  h1 .dot {
    width: 0.625rem;
    height: 0.625rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: #10b981;
  }
  .subtitle {
    color: #94a3b8;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
  }
  dl {
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: max-content 1fr;
    gap: 0.5rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
  dt {
    color: #94a3b8;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    align-self: center;
  }
  dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    word-break: break-all;
  }
  .note {
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0 0;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: #0f172a;
    border-left: 3px solid #38bdf8;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: #cbd5e1;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .note code {
    color: #fbbf24;
  }
  a { color: #60a5fa; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<main class="card">
  <h1><span class="dot"></span>SpatiumDDI Appliance</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">
    This appliance pairs with a remote control plane for role
    assignment (DNS, DHCP, …). There's no web UI here; this page
    just confirms the box is up and reachable. Role assignment +
    live config live in the Fleet UI on the control plane.
  </p>
  <dl>
    <dt>Hostname</dt>      <dd>__HOSTNAME__</dd>
    <dt>Control plane</dt> <dd><a href="__CONTROL_PLANE_URL__">__CONTROL_PLANE_URL__</a></dd>
    <dt>Version</dt>       <dd>__APPLIANCE_VERSION__</dd>
  </dl>
  <p class="note">
    To check live state — running pods, role assignment, heartbeat
    status — SSH in as the OS admin user you created at install and
    run <code>kubectl get pods -A</code>. For the full SpatiumDDI
    UI, browse to the control plane URL above.
  </p>
</main>
</body>
</html>
